name: ShippoCarrierProvider
description: Shippo helps you focus on growing your business. Start by connecting your e-commerce platform to Shippo to automatically sync order information. Then, create all shipping labels and docs you may need for domestic and international orders.

name: DeliverySolutionsCarrierProvider
description: DeliverySolutions

name: LRU Routing Provider
description: The LRU Routing Provider is designed to provide high level routing principles for one or many different instances of Fulfillment Providers. It controls order splitting policies and governs the Fulfillment Provider's routing priority phase by selecting a target Fulfillment Location using a Least Recently Used (LRU) selection algorithm.

displayName.fr-CA: Fournisseur de routage le moins récemment utilisé (MRU)

name: Multi-Segment Routing Provider
description: The Multi-Segment Routing Provider is designed to provide configurable multi-phase routing for one or many instances of fulfillment providers. It proceeds through a set of segments, each presenting individual conditions and configurations. Each segment has eligibility and priority and splitting configurations.

displayName.fr-CA: Segment avec fragmentation sur items complets

name: Competition Routing Provider
description: The Competition Routing Provider is designed to provide high level routing principles for one or many different instances of Fulfillment Providers. It controls the Fulfillment Provider's routing priority phase by selecting all eligible Fulfillment Locations and offering a shipment too all of them, at the same time, to elicit a competition to seize it. Competition routing does not support order splitting.

name: Buy-online-pick-up-in-store (Load Balanced)
description: The Buy-online-pick-up-in-store fulfillment provider is designed to complete the fulfillment process at specific pickup locations chosen by end users. It then governs polices associated with fulfillment concluding with the end customer picking up the shipment. For pure pickup scenarios, shipments are fulfilled using pickup locations' own inventory. For ship-to-store scenarios, fulfillment is handled by fulfillment locations and shipments are transferred to pickup locations chosen by customers. Ship-to-store fulfills orders using a fulfillment location different from the pickup location. Supported by its underlying Load Balanced Routing Provider, the fulfillment provider governs routing and fulfillment activities at both locations. The fulfilling end deals with picking, packing and transferring while the receiving end deals with pickers accepting shipments delivered to their pickup locations and concluding with the end customer picking up the shipment.

name: Buy-online-pick-up-in-store Short (Load Balanced)
description: The Buy-online-pick-up-in-store Short fulfillment provider is designed to complete the fulfillment process at specific pickup locations chosen by end users. For ship-to-store scenarios, fulfillment is handled by fulfillment locations and shipments are transferred to pickup locations chosen by customers. Ship-to-store fulfills orders using a fulfillment location different from the pickup location. Supported by its underlying Load Balanced Routing Provider, the fulfillment provider governs routing and fulfillment activities at both locations. The fulfilling end deals with picking, packing and transferring while the receiving end deals with pickers accepting shipments delivered to their pickup locations and concluding with the end customer picking up the shipment.

name: Ship from store (Load Balanced)
description: The Ship from Store Load Balanced Fulfillment Provider is designed to sequentially route order shipments, to ship to customers, to one of many fulfillment locations and to offer them for fulfillment. Routing is performed in two phases. The eligibility phase elects a group of fulfillment locations able to fulfill the order, or part of the order if more than one shipment per order is allowed. The priority phase then determines the next Fulfillment location to select for the shipment. The underlying Load Balanced Routing Provider controls splitting and prioritization. The provider then governs policies associated with in-store fulfillment, concluding with stores shipping the order shipments to the customer. Ship From Store fulfills orders using the fulfillment location’s own inventory.

name: External Refund
description: The External Refund Payment Provider is designed to present refunds issued outside the scope of a payment settlement processed within the Orckestra Commerce Platform. External refunds may be required when a refund is sent by mail or issued though credits in loyalty points.

name: TranssmartCarrierProvider
description: Transsmart allows you to easily connect your webshop, ERP and WMS to all your carriers! Control and optimize your shipment handling and transport costs from order entry until delivery. Connect your logistics services to your checkout and ERP/WMS with standard plugins.
